00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,267
And that's OK.

587
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,600
It's not necessarily everyone
has to learn the same way,

588
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:36,942
but it's really important
for those students who

589
00:22:36,942 --> 00:22:38,650
aren't able to do
everything on their own

590
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:39,660
that they come to class.

591
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:41,570
And we get a pretty
good attendance rate.

592
00:22:41,570 --> 00:22:43,870
And we think the clickers
help incentivize that.

593
00:22:43,870 --> 00:22:46,620
The piece that checker,
Jerry mentioned,

594
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:49,670
is a tool to get
students to know ahead

595
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:53,470
of time whether or not they
got their answer correct, so

596
00:22:53,470 --> 00:22:56,427
that they still have time
to reflect and ask a friend

597
00:22:56,427 --> 00:22:58,510
or think about it some
more while they might still

598
00:22:58,510 --> 00:22:59,176
get some credit.

599
00:22:59,176 --> 00:23:00,310
So there's still incentive.

600
00:23:00,310 --> 00:23:01,870
As opposed to a
couple weeks later,

